This is a NodeJs project

## Requirements

NodeJS >= 16.13.0
MongoDB >= 3.6 || Atlas mongodb database
neo4j

## install dependencies

```bash
npm install
# or
yarn install
```

## Configure env variables in config.env

```
PORT                port ex : 3001
NODE_ENV =              production || development
DATABASE =              database host ex : 'mongodb+srv://younesdb:<PASSWORD>@cluster0.dyw5w.mongodb.net/DeliveryNetwork?retryWrites=true&w=majority'

DATABASE_PASSWORD =       <PASSWORD> :   database password

TOKEN_TIMER =    10d      can be updated
TOKEN_SECRET = "This-is-my-secret-token-please-don't-touch"    token key  can be updated
JWT_COOKIE_EXPIRES_IN = 90   //can be updated

CLOUDINARY_URL=   cloudinary host url

CLOUDINARY_API = your api
CLOUDINARY_SECRET =  your secret
CLOUDINARY_USER_NAME=   user name


NEO4J_HOST =   neo4j host
NEO4J_USER=       user
NEO4J_PASSWORD =   password

SMTP_SERVICE =    smtp service case gmail
SMTP_EMAIL =    smtp email
SMTP_PASSWORD =    smtp password

```

## Launch server.js

```
npm start

```

## Read documentation of API

```
/api-docs

```

## .postman_collection file :

```
DeliveryNetwork.postman_collection.json


```
